    <h1>Pogba to stay ex&#xAD;tra year with United</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201018/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-18"><time>2020-10-18</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• Manch­ester United have trig­gered a one-year op­tion on Paul Pogba’s con­tract, ex­tend­ing the France mid­fielder’s deal un­til June 2022, the Bri­tish me­dia re­ported on Fri­day.</p>
    <p>The 27-year-old re­turned to United from Ju­ven­tus in a then world-record deal worth £89 mil­lion</p>
    <p>(S$156.2 mil­lion) in 2016 but he has suf­fered with in­con­sis­tent form and in­juries amid con­stant spec­u­la­tion over his fu­ture.</p>
    <p>The re­ports said United’s de­ci­sion to ex­tend his con­tract was taken be­fore Pogba said on in­ter­na­tional duty with France that he would love to play for Real Madrid one day.</p>


